<section id="slide2">
 <title>Slide 2:  History of Women at Rice </title>
 <list id="list2" list-type="bulleted">
	<item>Alice Crowell Dean was a teaching fellow in Math (and acting librarian) after graduating from the first class of Rice in 1916.
        </item>
	<item>It was not until 1950, that the first woman 
<cite target-id="drew"><cite-title>--Katherine Fischer Drew--</cite-title></cite> joined the faculty full time (History) and in 1962 was the first to achieve tenure.   She graduated from Rice in 1944.
        </item>
 </list>
 <figure id="Lombard_Laws">
  <title>The Lombard Laws</title>
  <media id="idm8803856" alt=""><image src="../../media/Lombard_Laws.jpg" mime-type="image/jpeg"/></media>
  <caption>
